title.narrative: Sao Paulo Sustainable Rural Development and Access to Markets

description.narrative: The project development objective is to support the Borrower in improving access to markets for rural producers organizations in its territory and in improving its instruments and policies that contribute to environmental sustainability of family agriculture.

condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :Schedule 2; Section I.A; 1 | Description :The Borrower shall, through CATI and CBRN, carry out the Project inaccordance with the Project Operational Manual, including the Procurement Plan, the Annual Operating Plans, the EnvironmentalManage | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2; Section I.A; 2, 3 and 4 | Description :The Borrower shall maintain, until the completion of theProject: (a) a joint CATI/CBRN Project management unit; (b) CATI and SMA Regional Units; and (c) a steering council | Frequency:Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2; Section I.A; 5 | Description :The Borrower shall convene, until the completion of the execution ofthe Project, a consultative forum at least once every year, and shall submit the proceedings of said meetings to the Bank |Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2; Section I.A; 6 | Description :The Borrower shall, at least once a year during Project implementationprepare and furnish to the Bank a plan for the Project#s operation during the following twelve months | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2; Section I.A; 7 | Description :The Borrower shall have all the procurement records and documentationfor the Subprojects for each fiscal year of the Project audited | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2; Section I.A; 8 | Description :The Borrower shall sign no later than twelve months after theEffective Date and thereafter maintain and comply with a memorandum of understanding with FUNAI | Due Date :31-Dec-2011

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2; Section I.C; 2 | Description :The Borrower shall make Grants to Beneficiaries for Subprojects inaccordance with eligibility criteria and procedures acceptable to the Bank as further detailed in the Project Operational Manual |Frequency :Quarterly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2; Section V; 1 and 2 | Description :The Borrower shall carry out jointly with the Bank a mid-termreview of the implementation of the Project and thereafter take any corrective action as recommended by the Bank | Due Date:28-Feb-2013
